    "The main reading materials were economics articles and textbooks, such as Law and Economics by Robert Cooter and Thomas Ulen, and Exchange and Production by Armen Alchian and William Allen.",
    "10 Manne (1993) writes: These courses for federal judges have been so popular that for most new judges today the Economics Institute is thought to be almost a requirement.",
    "The material on criminal law was based on the Becker model and deterrence theory.",
    "There was no material on behavioral economics nor on more sophisticated law-andeconomics theories, such as over-deterrence, according to the syllabi listed in Butler (1999).",
